            <bullet_list bullet="-" classes="classref-property-setget">
                <list_item>
                    <paragraph><abbreviation explanation="No return value.">void</abbreviation> <strong>set_engine_force</strong>(value: <reference internal="True" refuri="class_float#class-float"><inline classes="std std-ref">float</inline></reference>)</paragraph>
                </list_item>
                <list_item>
                    <paragraph><reference internal="True" refuri="class_float#class-float"><inline classes="std std-ref">float</inline></reference> <strong>get_engine_force</strong>()</paragraph>
                </list_item>
            </bullet_list>
            <paragraph>Accelerates the vehicle by applying an engine force. The vehicle is only sped up if the wheels that have <reference internal="True" refuri="class_vehiclewheel3d#class-vehiclewheel3d-property-use-as-traction"><inline classes="std std-ref">VehicleWheel3D.use_as_traction</inline></reference> set to <literal>true</literal> and are in contact with a surface. The <reference internal="True" refuri="class_rigidbody3d#class-rigidbody3d-property-mass"><inline classes="std std-ref">RigidBody3D.mass</inline></reference> of the vehicle has an effect on the acceleration of the vehicle. For a vehicle with a mass set to 1000, try a value in the 25 - 50 range for acceleration.</paragraph>
            <paragraph><strong>Note:</strong> The simulation does not take the effect of gears into account, you will need to add logic for this if you wish to simulate gears.</paragraph>
            <paragraph>A negative value will result in the vehicle reversing.</paragraph>
